Author-Name: Pedro Carneiro  
Author-Name: Sokbae Lee  
Title: Trends in Quality-Adjusted Skill Premia in the United States, 1960-2000 
Abstract:
 This paper presents new evidence that increases in college enrollment lead
 to a decline in the average quality of college graduates between 1960 and
 2000, resulting in a decrease of 6 percentage points in the college
 premium. A standard demand and supply framework can qualitatively account
 for the trend in the college and age premia over this period, but
 substantial quantitative adjustments are needed to account for changes in
 quality. (JEL I23, J24, J31)
