Author-Name: Joseph E. Harrington  
Author-Name: Andrzej Skrzypacz  
Title: Private Monitoring and Communication in Cartels: Explaining Recent Collusive Practices 
Abstract:
 Motivated by recent cartel practices, a stable collusive agreement is
 characterized when firms' prices and quantities are private information.
 Conditions are derived whereby an equilibrium exists in which firms
 truthfully report their sales and then make transfers within the cartel
 based on these reports. The properties of this equilibrium fit well with
 the cartel agreements in a number of markets including citric acid,
 lysine, and vitamins. (JEL D43, D82, K21, L12, L61, L65)
