Author-Name: Jesus Fernandez-Villaverde  
Author-Name: Pablo Guerron-Quintana  
Author-Name: Juan F. Rubio-Ramirez  
Author-Name: Martin Uribe  
Title: Risk Matters: The Real Effects of Volatility Shocks 
Abstract:
 We show how changes in the volatility of the real interest rate at which
 small open emerging economies borrow have an important effect on variables
 like output, consumption, investment, and hours. We start by documenting
 the strong evidence of time-varying volatility in the real interest rates
 faced by four emerging economies: Argentina, Brazil, Ecuador, and
 Venezuela. We estimate a stochastic volatility process for real interest
 rates. Then, we feed this process in a standard small open economy
 business cycle model. We find that an increase in real interest rate
 volatility triggers a fall in output, consumption, investment, hours, and
 debt. (JEL E13, E20, E32, E43, F32, F43, 011)
