Author-Name: Stefano Eusepi  
Author-Name: Bruce Preston  
Title: Expectations, Learning, and Business Cycle Fluctuations 
Abstract:
 This paper develops a theory of expectations-driven business cycles based
 on learning. Agents have incomplete knowledge about how market prices are
 determined and shifts in expectations of future prices affect dynamics.
 Learning breaks the tight link between fundamentals and equilibrium
 prices, inducing periods of erroneous optimism or pessimism about future
 returns to capital and wages which subsequent data partially validate. In
 a real business cycle model, the theoretical framework amplifies and
 propagates technology shocks. Moreover, it produces agents' forecast
 errors consistent with business cycle properties of forecast errors for a
 wide range of variables from the Survey of Professional Forecasters. (JEL
 C53, D83, D84, E32, E37)
